\N<Shopkeeper>Whether they're from Luda or not, a customer is a customer.
As long as I get paid, I'll provide the appropriate
hospitality.

\N<Shopkeeper>There's no point in being stubborn about it, after all, I've
got to make a living too.
<ActiveMessage:\C[10]■Event■>
\N<Segi>...

\N<Shopkeeper>What's the matter, standing there like that? If you've come
here, does that mean you've come to work?

\N<Shopkeeper>I was hoping you'd come. Sure, it might have been a series
of misfortunes for the missus, but I've made sure to provide
compensation for that.

\N<Segi>I... I didn't come here intending to sell my heart along
with my labor for a reward.

\N<Shopkeeper>I understand, you and our shop are in the same boat. That's
why I want to help you out for your sake.

\N<Shopkeeper>Well, that's how it is. Are you convinced? As usual, I've
prepared a change of clothes upstairs, so I'm counting on
you, okay?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Shopkeeper>What's the matter, standing there like that? If you've come
here, does that mean you've come to work?
\N<Segi>But...

\N<Shopkeeper>Ah, are you talking about last time? Well, in this line of
business, all sorts of things happen at the drinking table.

\N<Shopkeeper>But still, you came here despite that. Isn't that your
answer? It's none other than yourself who needs to earn a
living here, right?
\N<Segi>That is...

\N<Shopkeeper>I said I wouldn't get involved in your personal
circumstances. Of course, serving here isn't something I'd
force on you.

\N<Shopkeeper>Well, that's how it is. Are you convinced? As usual, I've
prepared a change of clothes upstairs, so I'm counting on
you, okay?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Shopkeeper>Hey there, glad you came, missus. I was hoping you'd come
again.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Shopkeeper>Haha, you won't attract customers with such a gloomy face.
You've got to be brighter if you're going to be out in front
of people, right?

\N<Shopkeeper>Of course, I won't get involved in your personal
circumstances. I have no intention of sticking my nose into
unnecessary matters. Our relationship is strictly business.

\N<Shopkeeper>Haha, feeling relieved? As usual, I've prepared a change of
clothes upstairs, so I'm counting on you, okay?
\N<Segi>Um...

\N<Shopkeeper>Glad you came again, missus. Just between us, I actually
thought you would come.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Shopkeeper>Ah, rest assured. I'm not interested in your personal
circumstances.

\N<Shopkeeper>The issue is that the missus can attract customers. And I
can reward that accordingly. That's what's important.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Shopkeeper>Shall we get straight to business then? Although this time
there's no need for you to go gathering materials. What I
need from you is just your service. Of course, the reward
will be generous.

\N<Segi>Wait, please. I haven't yet said that I would take the
job...
\N<Shopkeeper>...Is that so?
\N<Segi>...Yes.
\N<Shopkeeper>Hahaha, let's forget about the troublesome stuff for now.

\N<Shopkeeper>Like I said before, I can compensate for your work. And in
the way that you desire most... right?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Shopkeeper>Well, that's how it is. As usual, I've prepared a change of
clothes upstairs, so I'm counting on you, okay?
\N<Segi>Um...
\N<Shopkeeper>Hm? What is it, missus?

\N<Segi>That is... I saw the request board. If it's alright with
you, I was thinking maybe I could be of some help...
\N<Shopkeeper>The request board? You're going to take on a request?
\N<Segi>Yes, if it's alright with you, I would like to help out.

\N<Shopkeeper>That would be a great help. If it's the missus doing it,
it's all I could ask for.
\N<Segi>...?
\N<Shopkeeper>Then, let me explain the details of the request right away.
\N<Segi>Yes, please do.

\N<Shopkeeper>Although it's a simple matter. What I want to ask of you is
some easy assistance with customer service.

\N<Segi>Assistance with customer service... Understood. So what
should I do...?

\N<Shopkeeper>Yeah, so could you go upstairs for a bit? There are
preparations there.
\N<Segi>...?

\N<Shopkeeper>Well, I'll talk about the specifics later. For now, I'm
counting on you, okay?

\N<Shopkeeper>Let's forget about the troublesome stuff for now. Like I
said before, I can compensate for your hard work, and in the
way you desire most... right?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Shopkeeper>Well, that's how it is. As usual, I've prepared a change of
clothes upstairs, so I'm counting on you, okay?

\N<Shopkeeper>Whether they're from Luda or not, a customer is a customer.
As long as I get paid, I'll provide the appropriate
hospitality.

\N<Shopkeeper>There's no point in being stubborn about it, after all, I've
got to make a living too.

\N<Rozaro>Death row inmate Zozoie... I see, so he's the next opponent
for Miss Segi.
\N<Segi>Yes... You're already aware of him?

\N<Rozaro>Ah, he's a man who has quite a notorious reputation in those
circles. If I remember correctly, he was once the leader of
a band of bandits or something... I've heard he's like a
beast, not choosing his methods for his goals.

\N<Rozaro>Moreover, it seems he's extremely skilled in combat. There
are rumors that countless have fallen to his blade.
\N<Segi>...
\N<Rozaro>...I apologize. I didn't mean to make you anxious.

\N<Segi>Hehe, it's okay. I was prepared for this kind of thing when
I decided to join the military training meeting.

\N<Rozaro>...I see. Still, it's not appropriate to go into battle
without a plan. We'll have to prepare some sort of
countermeasure.
A

\N<Rozaro>Death row prisoner Zozie... It's not appropriate to go into
battle without a plan. We must prepare some sort of
countermeasure.
<ActiveMessage:\C[1]■Event■>

\N<Rozaro>Zozoie... I did a little digging on that guy. He's a
habitual rapist, and it seems he always targets women when
committing robbery or murder.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Rozaro>He probably thinks all women will bend to his will. But
that's exactly his blind spot; in other words, he's being
careless.
\N<Segi>Indeed... That might be true.

\N<Rozaro>You mustn't lose heart. You can do this. No... you must do
this.
B
\N<Rozaro>You mustn't lose heart. You can do it. No... you must do it.
<ActiveMessage:\C[1]■Event■>

\N<Rozaro>Hey, Segi-san. I've been thinking while you were coming
here... it seems we're indeed going to face quite a
troublesome opponent.

\N<Rozaro>Judging by their appearance, they don't seem like the type
to be reasoned with or to understand logic. Even if we think
of a strategy, it might be difficult.
\N<Segi>That's... true.

\N<Rozaro>Moreover... a death row inmate with numerous serious crimes.
No matter if it's for selecting robust soldiers in the
training association, why would someone like Zozoie be
allowed to participate?

\N<Segi>Well... from what I've heard, there seems to be a pardon
involved. Maybe they're using that as bait.

\N<Rozaro>I see. That's exactly something the people of Luda would
think of. That's why their fighting spirit is exceptionally
high.

\N<Rozaro>However... there's one thing I don't understand. How are
those people getting Zozoie to listen to them in the first
place?

\N<Rozaro>I hear he has an extremely belligerent personality. I wonder
if the promise of a pardon alone is enough to make him
obediently follow the Luda folks.
\N<Segi>Indeed... that's true.
C

\N<Rozaro>...There's something I don't understand. How exactly are
they getting those guys to listen to Zozoie in the first
place?

\N<Rozaro>I hear he's extremely belligerent by nature. Can a mere
promise of amnesty really be enough to make him obediently
follow Luda's people?
C

\N<Man>If you don't need anything, please don't talk to me.
Drinking here is the only way I can forget this harsh
reality...

\N<Man>The residents have started fighting each other at the
training sessions, and everyone's becoming more
aggressive... Perhaps it's part of the Luda group's aim.

\N<Man>Lately, even in a place like this, Luda's soldiers have
started showing up. I just want to drink my booze in
peace...

\N<Man>I don't have the strength to win matches, nor do I have the
power to train myself against monsters in the ruins. Is it
my fate to just die like this...

\N<Man>It's embarrassing to admit, but my wife and I have both
grown cold-hearted towards each other, and we no longer
function as a married couple.

\N<Man>And yet, why must I risk my life for her by participating in
the military training competition...
<ActiveMessage:\C[1]■Event■>

\N<Hojiko's Wife>Just when I got home a little while ago, I ran into my
husband. Ended up seeing his face when I least wanted to.

\N<Hojiko's Wife>And then, you know, his face was grinning more than usual.
Did something good happen to him or what?
\N<Segi>Well... I don't know, and it's none of my business.

\N<Hojiko's Wife>Hmph... I wonder? I just hope nothing strange happened while
I was away.
A
<ActiveMessage:\C[1]■Event■>

\N<Hojiko's Wife>Just when I got home a little while ago, I ran into my

\N<Hojiko's Wife>And then, you know, his face was grinning more than usual.
Did something good happen to him or what?

\N<Segi>I don't know... It's none of my business and I have no
relation to it.

\N<Hojiko's Wife>Hmph... I wonder? I just hope he hasn't gotten into some
strange business while I was away.
A

\N<Hojiko's Wife>Just when I got home a little while ago, I ran into my
husband. Ended up seeing his face, which I didn't even want
to see.

\N<Hojiko's Wife>And then, you know, his face was grinning more than usual.
Did something good happen or what?
